01:13:14,720 --> 01:13:22,560
none other than Sammy Jay. When at last Buster 
lay down for a nap, Sammy flew away, chuckling  

761
01:13:22,560 --> 01:13:29,600
to himself. "I believe I'll visit the Old 
Pasture to-morrow morning myself," thought he. "I  

762
01:13:29,600 --> 01:13:34,960
have an idea that something interesting may 
happen if Buster doesn't change his mind."

763
01:13:36,480 --> 01:13:42,080
Sammy was on the lookout very early the next 
morning. The first Jolly Little Sunbeams had  

764
01:13:42,080 --> 01:13:47,920
only reached the Green Meadows and had not started 
to creep into the Green Forest, when he saw a big,  

765
01:13:47,920 --> 01:13:52,720
dark form steal out of the Green 
Forest where it joins the Old Pasture.  

766
01:13:53,360 --> 01:13:57,360
It moved very swiftly and 
silently, as if in a great hurry.  

767
01:13:58,800 --> 01:14:04,080
Sammy knew who it was: it was Buster 
Bear, and he was going berrying.

768
01:14:04,800 --> 01:14:11,840
Sammy waited a little until he could see 
