770
01:14:18,160 --> 01:14:20,160
SOMEBODY ELSE GOES BERRYING

771
01:14:21,280 --> 01:14:26,400
Isn't it funny how two people will often 
think of the same thing at the same time,  

772
01:14:26,400 --> 01:14:32,080
and neither one know that the other is thinking of 
it? That is just what happened the day that Buster  

773
01:14:32,080 --> 01:14:38,000
Bear first thought of going berrying. While he 
was walking around in the Green Forest, talking to  

774
01:14:38,000 --> 01:14:43,840
himself about how hungry he was for some berries 
and how sure he was that there must be some up  

775
01:14:43,840 --> 01:14:50,000
in the Old Pasture, some one else was thinking 
about berries and about the Old Pasture too.

776
01:14:51,200 --> 01:14:54,240
"Will you make me a berry pie if 
I will get the berries to-morrow?"  

777
01:14:54,880 --> 01:14:57,120
asked Farmer Brown's boy of his mother.

778
01:14:58,000 --> 01:15:04,320
Of course Mrs. Brown promised that she would, 
and so that night Farmer Brown's boy went to bed  

779
01:15:04,320 --> 01:15:09,760
very early that he might get up early in the 
morning, and all night long he dreamed of berries  

780
01:15:09,760 --> 01:15:17,680
and berry pies. He was awake even before jolly, 
round, red Mr. Sun thought it was time to get up,  

