01:15:43,280 --> 01:15:48,640
and even extends a little way up on the Big 
Mountain. There is room in it for many people  

786
01:15:48,640 --> 01:15:54,640
to pick berries all day without even seeing each 
other, unless they roam about a great deal. You  

787
01:15:54,640 --> 01:15:59,440
see, the bushes grow very thick there, and 
you cannot see very far in any direction.  

788
01:16:00,400 --> 01:16:05,920
Jolly, round, red Mr. Sun had climbed a little 
way up in the sky by the time Farmer Brown's  

789
01:16:05,920 --> 01:16:11,760
boy reached the Old Pasture, and was smiling 
down on all the Great World, and all the Great  

790
01:16:11,760 --> 01:16:18,240
World seemed to be smiling back. Farmer Brown's 
boy started to whistle, and then he stopped.

791
01:16:19,440 --> 01:16:24,480
"If I whistle," thought he, 
"everybody will know just where I am,  

792
01:16:24,480 --> 01:16:29,440
and will keep out of sight, and I never can get 
acquainted with folks if they keep out of sight."

