01:29:58,880 --> 01:30:04,800
No wonder Sammy was excited. Blacky beat 
his wings fiercely and started after Sammy.

921
01:30:05,680 --> 01:30:11,440
And so they reached the edge of the Green Forest, 
Buster Bear running as hard as ever he could,  

922
01:30:11,440 --> 01:30:17,920
Sammy Jay flying just behind him and screaming, 
"Thief, thief, thief!" at the top of his lungs,  

923
01:30:17,920 --> 01:30:27,200
and behind him Blacky the Crow, trying to catch up 
and yelling as loud as he could, "Caw, caw, caw!  

924
01:30:27,200 --> 01:30:30,240
Come on, everybody! Come on! Come on!"

925
01:30:32,160 --> 01:30:38,560
Poor Buster! It was bad enough to be frightened 
almost to death as he had been up in the Old  

926
01:30:38,560 --> 01:30:43,520
Pasture when the pail had caught over his head 
just as Farmer Brown's boy had yelled at him.  

927
01:30:44,160 --> 01:30:49,440
Then to have the handle of the pail slip 
down around his neck so that he couldn't  

928
01:30:49,440 --> 01:30:55,360
get rid of the pail but had to take it with 
him as he ran, was making a bad matter worse.  

929
01:30:56,000 --> 01:31:02,800
Now to have all his neighbors of the Green 
Forest see him in such a fix and make fun of him,  

930
01:31:02,800 --> 01:31:10,560
was more than he could stand. He felt 
humiliated. That is just another way of saying  

931
01:31:10,560 --> 01:31:16,320
shamed. Yes, Sir, Buster felt that he 
was shamed in the eyes of his neighbors,  

932
01:31:16,320 --> 01:31:22,160
and he wanted nothing so much as to get away 
